{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"975adc59-c179-4a74-9eaf-a2a75a3efb89","content":"Here's what you need:\n\n### Environment Variables\n\nFor NativeAOT, you must explicitly point to `createdump` since it's not bundled with the runtime:\n\n```yaml\nenv:\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump\n    value: \"1\"\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType\n    value: \"4\"                          # Full dump (1=Normal, 2=WithHeap, 3=Triage, 4=Full)\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName\n    value: /tmp/dumps/core.%p.%t\n  - name: DOTNET_CreateDumpDiagnostics\n    value: \"1\"                          # Optional: logs createdump activity to stderr\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath\n    value: /opt/tools/createdump\n```\n\n### Pod Spec Changes\n\n```yaml\nspec:\n  containers:\n    - name: your-app\n      # ... your image, ports, etc.\n      securityContext:\n        capabilities:\n          add: [\"SYS_PTRACE\"]       # Required: createdump uses ptrace\n      volumeMounts:\n        - name: crash-dumps\n          mountPath: /tmp/dumps\n  volumes:\n    - name: crash-dumps\n      emptyDir:\n        sizeLimit: 2Gi              # Adjust based on app memory footprint\n```\n\n### Key points\n\n- **`SYS_PTRACE`** — required; `createdump` uses `ptrace` to read process memory.\n- **`DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath`** — critical for NativeAOT since createdump isn't in the default runtime location.\n- **`emptyDir`** — dumps are ephemeral; swap to a **PVC** or a sidecar that ships dumps to blob storage if you need persistence across pod restarts.\n- **`sizeLimit`** — full dumps (`Type=4`) can be as large as your app's RSS; size the volume accordingly. Use `Type=1` (Normal) for smaller dumps if you only need stack traces.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4b8329d2-0383-4410-a970-cfdf7ee365b7","outputTokens":516,"requestId":"6098:7D115:2CD6F6:3ABC38:69FFE43F"},"id":"4cf34527-b696-4a08-8366-64f94a8f6d2c","timestamp":"2026-05-10T01:50:02.776Z","parentId":"38583e8d-6e1d-43b9-8e95-307f1fe80fa2"}
